item.title: [Pi] Orphaned case error
item.dc:creator: @Ruby_Forums_Coder Ruby
item.description:
@Ruby_Forums_Coder wrote:

Please do some research before posting stuff such as this.

An orphaned case is simply a case that has been placed outside of the switch statement.

switch (example) {
        case 1:
                //Stuff
        break; 

        case 2:
                //Stuff
        break;
}
        case 3:
                //Orphaned Case
        break;

Should be

switch (example) {
        case 1:
                //Stuff
        break; 

        case 2:
                //Stuff
        break;
        case 3:
                //Orphaned Case
        break;
}

Read full topic
